Polypore Surges 13% in N.Y. Premarket Trading After Profit Beats Estimates

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-05-05T13:41:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/polypore-surges-13-in-n-y-premarket-trading-after-profit-beats-estimates.html
Polypore International Inc. (PPO) , the maker
of a key component in electric-car batteries, climbed to a
record after reporting first-quarter net income rose 47 percent,
beating analyst estimates.  The shares increased $7.33, or 13 percent, to $62.70 as of
9:33 a.m. on the New York Stock Exchange. Earlier, they reached
as high as $63.45, the highest for the  Charlotte , North
Carolina-based maker of battery membranes since trading began on
June 27, 2007.  Net income was $25.7 million, or 55 cents a share, up from
$17.5 million, or 38 cents, a year earlier, the company said in
a statement yesterday after the close of regular U.S. trading.
Polypore was expected to earn 39 cents, the average of five
analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  (Polypore plans to discuss results on a conference call with
analysts and investors today at 9 a.m. in  New York . To listen,
go to their web site at  http://www.polypore.net )  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Martin in New York at 
